5) Analysis:
•	Tables of name, order count, units sold and revenue of both cookie products and customers for 2020.
•	Line and clustered column chart showing the monthly revenue and count of orders for oatmeal raisin cookies for ACME Bites in 2020 (plus chocolate chip & cookies in a slicer)

6) Key Insights:
•	ACME Bites generates the 83.71% more revenue and makes 69.11% more orders, followed by Wholesome Foods. 
•	Chocolate Chip is the leading product generating 37.41% higher revenue.
•	Oatmeal Raisin is second best for ACME Bites.
•	White Chocolate Macadamia Nut was second for Wholesome Foods, 26.7% higher revenue.
•	ACME Bites sales for both products peak mid-year, with Chocolate Chip having 52% higher monthly orders. 
•	Chocolate Chip peaks in December for Wholesome Foods, while White Chocolate Macadamia Nut peaks mid-year but is less frequently ordered.

